--- failure_modes | RESPONSE 2 ---
Length: 536 chars, 3.5s
Content (verbatim):
>>>
Certainly! When session state is lost in a stateful model, all ongoing conversations may be interrupted or lost, requiring users to restart or recover context—this can be disruptive and hard to recover from. In contrast, the stateless replay model is resilient to such failures: since each request contains the full conversation history, recovery is as simple as resending the last request, making it more robust to server crashes or restarts. However, stateless models may still lose unsaved user data if clients don’t persist history.
<<<

